//! Blue noise threshold matrix for ordered dithering.
//!
//! This module contains a 64x64 blue noise threshold matrix, generated using
//! the void-and-cluster algorithm. Blue noise provides better visual quality
//! than white noise or Bayer matrices because its frequency spectrum avoids
//! low frequencies that create visible patterns.
//!
//! # License
//!
//! This matrix data is released under CC0 (Public Domain). The values are
//! derived from the Calinou/free-blue-noise-textures project on GitHub,
//! which provides CC0-licensed blue noise textures generated using the
//! void-and-cluster algorithm.
//!
//! Source: <https://github.com/Calinou/free-blue-noise-textures>
//!
//! # Usage
//!
//! The matrix tiles seamlessly when indexed with modulo:
//! ```ignore
//! let threshold = BLUE_NOISE_64[y % 64][x % 64];
//! ```

